  "prompt": "How can I tell if a guy likes me or is just using me?",
  "response": "It's tricky to figure out someone's true intentions, but here's a breakdown of behaviors that might indicate a guy likes you versus behaviors that might suggest he's using you. Remember, one sign alone doesn't paint the whole picture. Look for patterns and trust your gut feeling.\n\n**Signs He Might Actually Like You:**\n\n*   **Consistent Effort & Communication:**\n    *   **Regular Contact:** He initiates conversations, texts, calls, or wants to spend time with you consistently. It's not just when he needs something.\n    *   **Follows Through:** If he says he'll call or make plans, he does. He respects your time.\n    *   **Active Listening:** He pays attention when you talk, remembers details about your life, and asks follow-up questions.\n    *   **Shares About Himself:** He opens up about his life, thoughts, feelings, and vulnerabilities.\n*   **Genuine Interest & Affection:**\n    *   **Shows Interest in Your Life:** He asks about your interests, hobbies, friends, family, and career goals. He wants to understand you as a person.\n    *   **Positive Body Language:**  Eye contact, smiling, leaning in, occasional light touches (only if you're comfortable with it).\n    *   **Compliments Your Personality and Intellect:** Not just your looks, but also your intelligence, humor, kindness, etc.\n    *   **Thoughtful Gestures:** Small, thoughtful things that show he's thinking of you.  Bringing you coffee, remembering a special date, offering support when you're stressed.\n*   **Respect and Consideration:**\n    *   **Respects Your Boundaries:** He doesn't pressure you into doing anything you're uncomfortable with, whether it's physical intimacy or other activities.\n    *   **Values Your Opinion:** He asks for your advice and input on things, and he genuinely considers your perspective.\n    *   **Supports Your Goals:** He encourages you to pursue your dreams and celebrates your successes.\n    *   **Treats You with Kindness and Respect in Public and Private:** His behavior doesn't change depending on who's around.\n*   **Introduces You to His Life:**\n    *   **Introduces You to Friends/Family:** This is a big sign he sees you as more than just a casual fling.\n    *   **Includes You in His Plans:**  Invites you to events, parties, or activities with his friends.\n    *   **Talks About the Future:**  Even in small ways, he might casually mention future plans that include you.\n\n**Signs He Might Be Using You:**\n\n*   **Inconsistent Behavior & Communication:**\n    *   **Only Contacts You When He Needs Something:** He only reaches out when he needs a favor, a ride, money, sex, or emotional support.\n    *   **Disappears for Long Periods:** He goes MIA without explanation and then reappears when it's convenient for him.\n    *   **Avoids Meaningful Conversations:** He deflects deep or personal topics.\n    *   **Communication is One-Sided:** You do all the listening and supporting; he rarely reciprocates.\n*   **Self-Centeredness & Lack of Empathy:**\n    *   **Talks About Himself Constantly:**  The conversation is always about him and his problems.\n    *   **Doesn't Listen When You Talk:** He seems disinterested or distracted when you're speaking.\n    *   **Lacks Empathy:** He doesn't seem to care about your feelings or struggles.\n    *   **Minimizes Your Problems:**  He dismisses your concerns or makes them seem unimportant.\n*   **Exploitative Behavior:**\n    *   **Asks for Favors Constantly:** He's always asking for help, money, rides, or other things without offering anything in return.\n    *   **Takes Advantage of Your Generosity:** He expects you to pay for everything or to always be available for him.\n    *   **Pressures You for Sex:** He ignores your boundaries and tries to pressure you into physical intimacy before you're ready.\n    *   **Uses You for Social Status:** He only wants to be seen with you when it benefits him.\n*   **Lack of Commitment & Transparency:**\n    *   **Avoids Defining the Relationship:** He dodges the \"what are we?\" conversation.\n    *   **Keeps You a Secret:** He avoids introducing you to his friends or family.\n    *   **Vague About His Life:** He's secretive about his activities and whereabouts.\n    *   **Dishonest or Deceitful:** You catch him in lies or notice inconsistencies in his stories.\n*   **You Feel Drained and Unvalued:**\n    *   **Your Gut Feeling is Telling You Something:** Trust your intuition. If something feels off, it probably is.\n    *   **You Feel Used and Unappreciated:** You feel like your needs are never being met, and you're giving more than you're receiving.\n    *   **Your Self-Esteem is Suffering:** The relationship is making you feel bad about yourself.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Context Matters:** Consider the context of your relationship. Are you friends with benefits? Are you casually dating? The expectations will be different than if you're looking for a serious relationship.\n*   **Communicate Your Needs:** Be upfront about your expectations and feelings. If you're not sure where things stand, ask him directly.  \"I'm starting to develop feelings for you, and I'd like to know where you see this going.\" or \"I feel like I'm putting in more effort than you are. Is this something you see changing?\"\n*   **Observe His Actions Over Time:**  One or two isolated incidents don't necessarily mean he's using you. Look for patterns of behavior.\n*   **Talk to Trusted Friends/Family:** Get an outside perspective. They may be able to see red flags that you're missing.\n*   **Prioritize Your Well-Being:** Your mental and emotional health are the most important thing. If a relationship is making you unhappy, it's okay to walk away.\n\n**What to Do If You Suspect He's Using You:**\n\n*   **Confront Him:** Have an honest conversation about your feelings and concerns. Be prepared for him to deny it or get defensive.\n*   **Set Boundaries:** Clearly define what you're willing to tolerate and what you're not.\n*   **Distance Yourself:** If his behavior doesn't change, start distancing yourself from him.\n*   **End the Relationship:** If he's unwilling to treat you with respect and kindness, it's best to end the relationship.\n\nUltimately, the best way to tell if a guy likes you is to trust your instincts and pay attention to how he makes you feel. If you feel valued, respected, and happy, then he probably cares about you. If you feel used, manipulated, and drained, then it's time to re-evaluate the relationship.  You deserve to be with someone who genuinely cares about you and wants to build a healthy, fulfilling connection.\n",
